Merle neemt je mee op ondernemers avontuur zodat je slimmer gaat ondernemen, de snelle routes, loopholes en de shortcuts gaat ontdekken. Stel je voor dat alles kan?! Wat zou er dan mogelijk voor je zijn? Merle laat je zien dat het leven een groot experiment is en dat ALLES mogelijk is. Want als jij groeit als mens en ondernemer, kan je nog meer mensen helpen met je prachtige idee√´n, zodat je bedrijf gaat groeien, je meer impact maakt op de wereld en een verschil maakt in het leven van anderen. Welcome to Merle Talks: Stories of faith, love, and hope. My name is Merle Dawn Comidoy from the Philippines. I created this podcast to give inspiration to people who are suffering from depression. My father died because of depression on March 21, 2013. His death taught me valuable lessons and I am here to share those life lessons with you.  I am not perfect. I have sinned a lot and I'm constantly sinning but I always try my best to be a better individual than my past. I hope that these stories may inspire you. I would also love to know your stories by messaging me or commenting on my tracks. God bless you.

A gesta√ß√£o do que viria a ser o MERLIM come√ßou em meados de 1997, quando Felipe Lion fazia algumas sess√µes de grava√ß√£o no est√∫dio Quorum, em S√£o Paulo. Tratava-se apenas de um registro "voz & viol√£o" de m√∫sicas novas, cuja produ√ß√£o ficara a cargo do baterista e produtor Junior Gaspari ‚Äì antigo parceiro de Lion no Sex-Fanzine [uma obscura banda paulistana de Art Rock do come√ßo dos anos 90].

O est√∫dio era muito freq√ºentado por m√∫sicos da cena local e, ao final das grava√ß√µes, tinham se juntado a eles o baixista Z√© Luiz Zambianchi [aka Bol√£o] e o guitarrista Jaques Molina.

Juntos gravaram o primeiro EP da banda [Merlim], lan√ßado na casa de shows Popular [hoje, Na Mata Caf√©] em 5 de outubro de 1998. Em sua estr√©ia o MERLIM j√° contava com um quinto elemento, Guto Domingues, segundo guitarrista da banda. Pouco depois, Kike Damaceno entraria no lugar de Jaques.

Seguiram-se outros EPs: Tribal, 2000; Ruas Molhadas, 2001; Sem Ar, 2002; e Se For Falar das Flores, 2003. Finalmente, em 2008, depois de 10 anos de estrada, lan√ßam seu primeiro √°lbum "A Tempestade", produzido por Kiko Zambianchi.

Uma curiosidade: o MERLIM n√£o tinha baixista nessa √©poca. Todos os baixos do √°lbum foram feitos por m√∫sicos convidados - Lee Marcucci [Tutti Frutti, Radio Taxi, Gang 90, Titas], Kiko Zambianchi, Ney Haddad [PR5, Mobilis Stabilis, Caviars Blues Band], Jaques Molina.

Mesmo sem gravadora e seguindo uma pol√≠tica radicalmente autoral, o MERLIM manteve-se em constante atividade durante esse tempo, tocando em teatros, bares e casas noturnas de todos os tipos - dos mais bizarros inferninhos at√© as estreladas, como o Bourbon Street Music Club. Em 2007 fez uma s√©rie de shows para a Lee, famosa marca de jeans, que escolheu a banda para representar uma cole√ß√£o inspirada no Rock'n'Roll.

O pouco contato com a m√≠dia n√£o impediu algumas manifesta√ß√µes calorosas, de respeito ao trabalho da banda. Sobre o MERLIM, Kid Vinil disse: "N√£o √© apenas um som moderno, mas tem um sabor de anos 80, assim como uma antena no Britpop ingl√™s e as guitars band americanas". J√° Antonio Carlos Monteiro, editor da revista Rock Brigade, foi mais enf√°tico: "Melhor do que 99% do que se ouve nesse ramo".

A forma√ß√£o atual do MERLIM segue, desde 2010, com Felipe Lion nos vocais, Guto Domingues e Kike Damaceno nas guitarras, Thiago Consorti no baixo e J√∫nior Gaspari na bateria.

Merlin Mallet‚Äôs voice and his unique way of singing are like acoustic magnets ‚Äì there is no way to turn a deaf ear to it. He builds a bridge between spherical worlds and a rocking pop sound, the synthesizer and the guitar, between gentleness and strength. This charismatic singer guides us with magical intensity through his musical vernissage Behind Magic. 
Soft notes and colourful sound worlds, this is how Merlin Mallet presents himself in songs like Cosmic walk or You're like champagne. Should you now think that he is introverted and hopelessly romantic, you will be surprised by his powerful voice, moving rhythms and intense guitar chords when listening to Missing mails, Broken dreams and particularly Riche ch√©rie. 
Here, if not before, this album is leaving the familiar territory of a typical singer-songwriter production, embedding Merlin Mallet‚Äôs voice in meticulously precise sound patterns that are thoughtfully arranged.

Merlin Mallet combines music and painting, and only considers a song as truly completed after having painted it on canvas to make it eternal. His painting and his music complement each other in an unusually beautiful and direct way.

On his website www.merlin-mallet.com you have access to both his music and paintings.

The Raggle Taggle Band are a South Devon based band who play high energy traditional and contemporary Celtic, English, American and European folk music and song for weddings, pub gigs, barndances etc. Depending on the occasion we can do footstomping/hand clapping Irish Jigs, fun folk songs, slow reels, calm or rowdy!
 
Already we have forged a solid reputation for our live performance with a trademark mix of strong dynamics and driving rhythms. We do try to be different and innovation meets sensitivity as we push the conventional boundaries of traditional music yet remain sympathetic to its past, present and future, infecting the listener with a sense of musical delight ‚Äì magical, joyous and uplifting!
